  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Restore UI Design After Tailwind Migration\n\nFix visual and layout issues introduced during the migration to Tailwind CSS, ensuring the preschool website meets design standards with proper spacing, alignment, and visibility.\n\nRequirements:\n- Add visual separation between section elements (margins, borders, or background colors)\n- Fix hero image alignment to properly display at fullscreen/various viewport sizes\n- Restore menu visibility with appropriate contrast, positioning, and styling\n- Correct font casing on clickable elements (buttons, links, CTAs) to match design specs\n- Adjust padding and spacing on interactive elements for proper touch targets and visual balance\n- Ensure all changes maintain child-friendly, playful aesthetic appropriate for preschool audience\n- Test layout responsiveness across mobile, tablet, and desktop breakpoints\n- Verify color contrast meets accessibility standards for young children and parents\n\nEdge Cases to Consider:\n- Very wide screens (ultrawide monitors)\n- Mobile landscape orientation\n- Menu behavior on scroll (fixed/sticky positioning)\n- Interactive element states (hover, focus, active) for both mouse and touch users",
